    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hydrous sodium carbonate found in nature as evaporative residues. Used widely as a silica source in early glass manufacture; in ancient Egypt used as well as a bleach for linen, a preservative in mummification, and as an ingredient of incense. </Note_Text>
